      "technicalName": "AZOXYSTROBIN 4.8% + CHLOROTHALONIL 40% SC",
      "detailHtml": "<p><strong>TECHNICAL NAME: AZOXYSTROBIN 4.8% + CHLOROTHALONIL 40% SC</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>DESCRIPTION:&nbsp;</strong>AVONIL <strong>(AZOXYSTROBIN 4.8%+CHLOROTHALONIL 40% SC)</strong> mode of action is different from the action of other fungicidal groups and there is no known cross-resistance to this mode of action in pathogens which have developed reduced sensitivity to other fungicides.</p>\r\n<p><strong>MODE OF ACTION:&nbsp;AZOXYSTROBIN 4.8%+CHLOROTHALONIL 40% SC</strong> is a broad-spectrum systemic and contact fungicide.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATION:</strong></p>\r\n<table width=\"532\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"78\"><strong>Crops</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"278\"><strong>TARGET PEST/ DISEASE</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"157\"><strong>DOSE PER ACRE</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cucumber</td>\r\n<td width=\"278\">Downy Mildew, Leaf spot &amp; Powdery Mildew</td>\r\n<td>1200 ml/Acre</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cauliflower</td>\r\n<td width=\"278\">Downy Mildew, Leaf spot&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>1200 ml/Acre</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Watermelon</td>\r\n<td width=\"278\">Downy Mildew, Leaf spot &amp; Powdery Mildew</td>\r\n<td>1200 ml/Acre</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>PACKING SIZE:&nbsp;</strong>150 ml, 300 ml, 600 ml</p>\r\n<p><strong>FEATURES &amp; BENEFITS :</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>AVONIL (AZOXYSTROBIN 4.8%+CHLOROTHALONIL 40% SC) is used as a protective treatment or in the early stages of disease development.</li>\r\n<li>AVONIL has resistance management qualities which increases the yield of crop.</li>\r\n<li>AVONIL is recommended for the control of Downy Mildew, Leaf spot &amp; Powdery Mildew of Cucumber, Downy Mildew &amp; Leaf spot of Cauliflower and Downy mildew, Leaf spot &amp; Powdery Mildew of Watermelon.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>ANTIDOTE:&nbsp;</strong>No specific antidote is known treat symptomatically.</p>",
