      "technicalName": "Hexaconazole 5% EC",
      "detailHtml": "<p><strong>Technical Name:&nbsp;</strong>Hexaconazole 5% EC</p>\r\n<p><strong>Mode of Action: </strong>Hexaconazole is a <strong>systemic fungicide</strong> belonging to the <strong>triazole</strong><strong> group</strong>.</p>\r\n<table width=\"503\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"95\"><strong>Crop(s)</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"272\"><strong>TARGET PEST/ DISEASE</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"136\"><strong>DOSE PER ACRE</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Grapes</td>\r\n<td width=\"272\">Powdery mildew</td>\r\n<td>200-400 ml/Acre</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Mango</td>\r\n<td width=\"272\">Powdery mildew</td>\r\n<td>0.1% (100ml/100lit)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tea</td>\r\n<td>Blister Blight</td>\r\n<td>80 ml/Acre</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Rice</td>\r\n<td>Blast, Shealth blight</td>\r\n<td>400 ml/Acre</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Groundnut</td>\r\n<td>Tikka Leaf Spot</td>\r\n<td>600 ml/Acre</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Apple</td>\r\n<td>Scab</td>\r\n<td>0.05% (50ml/100lit)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Soybean</td>\r\n<td width=\"272\">Rust</td>\r\n<td>0.1% (100ml/100lit)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>Target Diseases:&nbsp; </strong>Sheath blight, Powdery mildew, Scab,&nbsp; Tikka, Leaf Spot</p>\r\n<p><strong>Packing Size: </strong>&nbsp;100 ml, 250 ml, 500 ml, 1 Ltr</p>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Controls multiple fungal diseases with a single product.</li>\r\n<li>Enhances crop yield and quality by minimizing fungal damage.</li>\r\n<li>Reduces the frequency of application due to long-lasting activity.</li>\r\n<li>Cost-effective for farmers due to its dual action and low dosage.</li>\r\n<li>Promotes healthy plant gr<strong>owth</strong> by protecting from fungal attacks.</li>\r\n</ul>",
