      "technicalName": "Triacontanol EW 0.1% Min.",
      "detailHtml": "<p><strong>Technical Name:</strong> Triacontanol EW 0.1% Min.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Packing Size: </strong>&nbsp;100 ml, 250 ml, 500 ml, 1 Ltr</p>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Boosts overall plant growth and biomass</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Enhances <strong>root development</strong>, leading to better nutrient uptake.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Improves flowering and fruit setting</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Increases <strong>yield quality and quantity</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Reduces <strong>stress effects</strong> from drought, temperature, or chemical exposure.</li>\r\n<li>Promotes <strong>uniform maturity</strong> and early harvest in many crops.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Dose</strong>: 1&ndash;2 ml per liter of water for foliar application.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Timing</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>First spray:&nbsp; At early vegetative stage.</li>\r\n<li>Second spray : At flowering or early fruit set stage.</li>\r\n<li>Third spray:&nbsp; During fruit development (if required).</li>\r\n</ul>",
